text: Momhil Sar is a mountain in the Karakoram range, in Pakistan. Momhil Sar is part of the Hispar Muztagh subrange. It is the 63rd highest mountain in the world. The first people to reach the top were Hans Schell and his expedition, in 1965. == References == Category:Mountains of Gilgit-Baltistan Category:Karakoram
title: Momhil Sar
